    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What does USDA Organic mean for gummy bears?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'USDA Organic certification for gummy bears means that at least 95% of the ingredients are certified organic — grown without synthetic pesticides, synthetic fertilizers, GMOs, artificial colors, or artificial flavors. The manufacturing facility must also meet organic handling standards. This is the highest standard for organic food products in the United States and requires annual third-party auditing.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Are organic gummy bears healthier than regular gummy bears?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Organic gummy bears eliminate synthetic pesticide residues, artificial dyes (Red 40, Yellow 5, Blue 1), and artificial flavors from the equation. They are not necessarily lower in sugar or calories — organic cane sugar is still sugar. The health advantage is in ingredient quality and the absence of synthetic chemicals, not in macronutrient composition. For reduced sugar, look specifically for brands like SmartSweets.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Are organic gummy bears vegan?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Not always. USDA Organic certification addresses farming practices, not animal-derived ingredients. An organic gummy bear can still contain organic gelatin (from grass-fed cattle) or organic beeswax. Most organic gummy bear brands on the market today use pectin instead of gelatin, but you should verify by checking the ingredient list or looking for a separate Certified Vegan logo.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Why are organic gummy bears more expensive?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Organic ingredients cost more to produce due to organic farming certification requirements, lower crop yields without synthetic fertilizers, and the cost of organic handling and processing facilities. Organic cane sugar, organic pectin, and organic fruit juice concentrates each carry a premium over their conventional equivalents. However, brands like Black Forest and YumEarth have achieved scale that keeps prices competitive with mainstream candy.' },
    },
