    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Do organic gummy bears taste different from regular gummy bears?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Organic gummy bears often taste more "natural" and less artificially sweet because they use real fruit juice and organic cane sugar instead of high-fructose corn syrup and artificial flavors. The colors are more muted (natural colorants are less vibrant than synthetic dyes). Most consumers describe the taste as more authentic and fruit-forward, though some prefer the bolder, more uniform taste of conventional candy.' },
    },
  ],
};
