    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="faq-sec">
      <h2>Organic Gummy Bears — Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What does USDA Organic mean for gummy bears?</summary><p>95%+ organic ingredients, no synthetic pesticides, no GMOs, no artificial colors or flavors. Requires annual third-party auditing of ingredients, supply chains, and manufacturing.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are organic gummy bears healthier than regular gummy bears?</summary><p>They eliminate synthetic dyes and artificial flavors, but organic sugar is still sugar. The health advantage is ingredient quality and absence of synthetic chemicals, not lower calories or sugar.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are organic gummy bears vegan?</summary><p>Most are, but not all. USDA Organic does not guarantee vegan. Check for gelatin or beeswax in the ingredient list, or look for a separate Certified Vegan logo.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Why are organic gummy bears more expensive?</summary><p>Organic farming costs more due to certification, lower yields, and organic processing requirements. Brands like Black Forest and YumEarth have achieved scale that keeps prices near conventional candy levels.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What artificial dyes are in regular gummy bears?</summary><p>Red 40, Yellow 5, Blue 1, and other petroleum-derived FD&C colors. These are linked to hyperactivity in children and require warning labels in the EU. Organic gummy bears use turmeric, carrot, beetroot, and fruit concentrates instead.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Where can I buy organic gummy bears?</summary><p>Whole Foods, Amazon, Target, Sprouts, Natural Grocers, and most health food stores. YumEarth and Black Forest have the widest distribution including conventional grocery chains.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are organic gummy bears gluten-free?</summary><p>Most are. YumEarth, Surf Sweets, Black Forest Organic, and Annie's are all certified gluten-free. Check labels for cross-contamination warnings.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Do organic gummy bears taste different from regular gummy bears?</summary><p>They taste more "natural" and fruit-forward because they use real fruit juice instead of artificial flavors. Colors are more muted. Most consumers describe the taste as more authentic.</p></details>
    </section>

